main event: On July 22, 1954, multiple reports were made of an unidentified aerial object seen in Coronado, California, traveling at an extreme rate of speed and making an unusual sound.
interesting points: The object was estimated to be at an altitude of 1500 feet and appeared round, white, and luminous.
The witnesses had extensive military aviation experience and stated that the object's sound did not match any aircraft or known aerial phenomenon.
No similar reports were received, and no action was taken as a result of the reports by the District Office.
Despite the lack of conclusive evidence, the witnesses felt that the matter was important enough to report due to the unidentified nature of the object.
The report was sent to the Air Technical Intelligence Center and the Director of Special Investigations at the Headquarters USAF in Washington, D.C.
witnesses: Major General Walter G. Farrell, U.S. Marine Corps (Retired), and other military personnel
photographs: no photographs were included in the report
